    "body": "We do have `teku transition` which can take a pre state and apply either blocks or empty slots to produce the resulting post state. That assumes the state and blocks are local files - it could be quite useful to update it to support being given the URL to an archive node (or Infura) and a start and end slot then have it download the pre state and blocks itself.  If we do that it probably should save those downloaded states/blocks locally as well to make rerunning faster and make it easier to then inspect their contents.",
